{"word":"δίαιτα","slug":"δίαιτα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δίαιτα</b></el> <el>(δίαιτα, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>prob. from <a href='S:ζάω'><el>ζάω</el></a> \n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a way of living, mode of life</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>δ. ποιεῖσθαι</el> to pass <i>one's life</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a dwelling, abode, room</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>at Athens, <i>arbitration</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b>Oratt.</b><p/></div>"}]}